Date: Thu, 8 Jan 2026 17:38:43 +0200
Subject: Stop depending on Python packages storpool and storpool.spopenstack

Since [1] got merged the Python packages 'storpool' and
'storpool.spopenstack' are no longer required for communication with a
StorPool system.

[1]: https://review.opendev.org/c/openstack/cinder/+/933078

Change-Id: I01a7a52bc48be5aa86535a2844866c57a9cc3274
Signed-off-by: Biser Milanov <biser.milanov@storpool.com>
---
 driver-requirements.txt | 4 ----
 pyproject.toml          | 2 --
 2 files changed, 6 deletions(-)

diff --git a/driver-requirements.txt b/driver-requirements.txt
index 8d78e3087..5d60a5097 100644
--- a/driver-requirements.txt
+++ b/driver-requirements.txt
@@ -41,10 +41,6 @@ capacity # BSD
 infi.dtypes.wwn # PSF
 infi.dtypes.iqn # PSF
 
-# Storpool
-storpool>=7.1.0 # Apache-2.0
-storpool.spopenstack>=2.2.1 # Apache-2.0
-
 # Datera
 dfs_sdk>=1.2.25 # Apache-2.0
 
diff --git a/pyproject.toml b/pyproject.toml
index 4eb0f976e..6a667c24d 100644
--- a/pyproject.toml
+++ b/pyproject.toml
@@ -87,8 +87,6 @@ all = [
     "infinisdk>=103.0.1", # BSD-3
     "py-pure-client>=1.47.0", # BSD
     "rsd-lib>=1.1.0", # Apache-2.0
